<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{6}{y}=-{18}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{9}{x}-{4}{y}={22}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{1}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{6}{y}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{18}-{\left({6}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{18}-{\left({6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{\left(\frac{{-{18}-{\left({6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{6}}}}\right)}+-{4}{y}={22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{9}}{{-{{6}}}}\cdot{\left(-{18}\right)}-\frac{{9}}{{-{{6}}}}{\left({6}\right)}{y}+-{4}{y}={22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{27}-{\left({9}\right)}{y}+-{4}{y}={22}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{y}+{\left(-{4}\right)}{y}={22}-{27}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{y}+{\left(-{4}\right)}{y}=-{5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({9}+{\left(-{4}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{y}=-{5}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{5}}{{5}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{1}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{6}{\left(-{1}\right)}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}+{\left(-{6}\right)}=-{18}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{18}-{\left(-{6}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{6}{x}=-{12}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{12}}{{-{{6}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},-{1}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

